==English==

===Verb===
'''[[light]] [[a]] [[fire]] [[under]] (someone)'''

# {{idiom}} To [[motivate]] or encourage (someone) to start sooner or move faster.
#: ''Let me see if I can '''light a fire under''' the waiter to get our order sooner.''

===Usage notes===

The origin of the phrase came from when [[chimney sweep]]s were scared to go up the chimneys, the fire would be lit under them in order to motivate them to climb to the top.